(952, 2000000043, 'es over the traditional waterfall model that involves lengthy development and testing phases.\n*   Ultimately, DevOps focuses on meeting user demands for innovative features and consistent performance. - IBM\n\n#### 1.8.1 DevOps Life-Cycle\n\n*   Source: [https://www.ibm.com/think/topics/devops](https://www.ibm.com/think/topics/devops)\n\n#### 1.8.2 DevOps Life-Cycle\n\n##### Planning\n\n*   Teams identify new features and functions for upcoming releases, using user feedback and insights from internal stakeholders like engineers and compliance teams. The objective is to create a prioritized backlog of features, improvements, and bug fixes.\n\n##### Coding\n\n*   The DevOps team develops features from the backlog using common practices like test-driven development (TDD), pair programming, and peer code reviews. Code is initially written and tested on local workstations before advancing in the continuous delivery pipeline.\n    *   Source: [https://www.ibm.com/think/topics/devops](https://www.ibm.', '[0.010641396,-0.018102057,-0.024715768,-0.026534747,0.012632636,0.0049285106,0.010040701,0.07145631,-0.016001835,-0.05578973,-0.050123695,0.022078069,0.0444613,0.048138622,-0.0052632005,-0.026917696,0.016696863,0.07097756,-0.027253276,0.02765924,-0.000286262,-0.00021337245,-0.015379597,-0.0648365,-0.013204718,-0.08640088,0.042372104,-0.020123256,0.022626167,-0.0039490596,-0.015553592,0.0102108745,0.023633443,-0.013291296,-0.0135282595,-0.015176458,0.018226538,-0.013373816,0.028102318,-0.015093624,-0.044122882,-0.033697356,-0.077959135,0.078934304,-0.010285571,0.036668003,-0.017975,0.021728376,-0.011225172,0.016047804,-0.0002303698,0.023782145,-0.0010690374,0.05246369,-0.017898954,-0.038764987,-0.0019680734,-0.036270045,0.025054993,0.011917942,-0.011424094,-0.024043849,-0.007444565,-0.05724632,0.021041187,0.03400025,-0.033840384,-0.030870842,0.030294819,0.014438594,-0.012333888,0.026506254,-0.014488928,0.038796134,-0.014583149,0.028798154,-0.01444416,-0.