(969, 2000000044, 'ssment\n*   Disaster recovery plan\n*   Evaluated and determined RPO and RTO\n\n### Key Takeaways: Disaster Planning Strategies\n\n*   Failures can occur at any time and on a small, large, or global scale.\n*   A disaster recovery plan will help limit business and customer impact when a disaster occurs.\n*   RPO is the maximum acceptable amount of data loss after an unplanned data-loss incident.\n*   RTO is the amount of time an application, system, and process can be down without causing significant damage to the business.\n*   A BCP is a system of prevention and recovery from potential threats to a company that includes RPO and RTO.\n\n## 7. AWS Disaster Recovery Planning\n\n### DR Plans Span More Than One Region\n\n*(Diagram showing Region 1 and Region 2 with components like Storage, Compute, Database, Management & Governance, Networking & Content Delivery)*\n\n### Storage and Backup Building Blocks', '[0.06428872,0.011024828,-0.030071603,-0.017611917,0.017348576,0.048186887,0.05257404,-0.043536372,-0.022486404,0.021510573,0.00087285903,0.04292879,0.006344427,-0.0066302707,0.043625195,-0.037378073,0.10825797,0.010150266,-0.046135306,-0.04414908,0.001464768,-0.055510283,-0.008217236,-0.06428757,-0.018637266,-0.08815756,-0.028477386,-0.03596425,0.008622786,-0.047888502,-0.0060728714,-0.03367655,-0.011525522,-0.019984176,0.005954202,0.040146794,0.022426864,-0.0062520574,0.014799626,-0.015822742,-0.030474512,0.010514571,-0.052244194,0.051260006,-0.023921983,-0.008530081,-0.05276812,0.08096124,-0.058595598,0.010016722,0.02436951,0.017699221,-0.017859759,0.04097212,0.03461479,-0.098904796,0.004761351,-0.06107487,0.009100155,0.010262634,-0.01322512,0.010881459,0.03451401,-0.017886445,0.037160803,-0.003750137,0.003432077,-0.0038473385,-0.029697806,0.004855362,-0.0028353208,0.068570055,0.005673126,0.030328754,-0.02042802,0.01350541,0.018200638,-0.023644995,-0.02129142,0.027839907,0.02563679,0.007263853,0.116644844,0.0043465137,0.04478718,-0.002062496,0.