(977, 2000000044, 'Bring up resources around the replicated core dataset.\n    *   Then scale the system as needed to handle current production traffic.\n    *   Switch over to the new system.\n\n### Warm Standby Pattern\n\n*(Diagram showing AWS Cloud with a secondary DB, primary DB, low capacity web servers and app servers in an auto-scaling group, and Route 53)*\n\n### Implementing Warm Standby Pattern\n\n*   **Preparation phase:**\n    *   Is similar to pilot light.\n    *   Has all necessary components running 24/7, but not scaled for production traffic.\n    *   Need to conduct continuous testing on components.\n*   **In case of disaster:**\n    *   Failover most critical production load immediately.\n    *   Scale the system further to handle all production load (automatically).\n\n### Multi-Site Pattern\n\n*(Diagram showing AWS Cloud with a secondary DB, primary DB, full capacity web servers and app servers in auto-scaling groups, and Route 53)*\n\n### Implementing Multi-Site Pattern\n\n*   **Preparation phase:**', '[0.052869484,0.028299082,-0.04064093,0.002818006,0.038529843,0.013220959,0.047029793,0.02148515,-0.037957925,-0.029493062,-0.010781302,0.06993177,0.022269912,0.0071416255,-0.0038574024,-0.03527046,0.05022949,0.054827627,-0.0049485774,-0.01629073,0.020887893,0.021975625,-0.005126821,-0.07951359,-0.046250347,-0.009020879,0.010975195,-0.0014128771,0.030592494,-0.02872335,0.014372117,-0.0042889174,0.03434954,-0.012493989,0.00073794794,0.004649201,0.0012521531,0.034121636,-0.0042691566,-0.025345104,-0.06736059,0.03617826,-0.047941577,0.05869557,0.005305294,0.00814978,-0.016381584,0.045809217,-0.05428029,0.0037114988,0.034046873,-0.0030057253,-0.004112839,0.006434769,0.018209614,-0.07248068,-0.005383908,-0.021747759,-0.026652459,-0.0123191485,-0.041517314,-0.0025809598,0.010271621,0.012084959,0.04464463,0.010686258,-0.056505404,0.009251255,0.008912466,0.00803411,0.014393801,0.07081884,0.01414548,0.031682044,-0.020789485,-0.0027197422,0.011915013,-0.0220