(90, 10, 'Summarization\'s Impact on Sentiment Preservation', 'This study aims to systematically evaluate how text summarization, specifically at varying compression ratios and using both extractive and abstractive methods, affects sentiment preservation. By employing sentiment-labelled datasets and analyzing generated summaries with a pretrained classifier, the research will measure accuracy loss, polarity flip rates, and confidence changes. The goal is to identify which summarization techniques and compression levels best maintain sentiment integrity, offering practical guidance for sentiment-sensitive applications and contributing to the development of more reliable NLP pipelines.', '2025-11-09 15:40:32'),
(95, 37, 'Software Maintenance: Evolution, Sustainment, and DevOps', 'The BMSE3014 Software Maintenance course focuses on the evolution and sustainment of software systems, crucial for adapting to changing user needs and environments. Software maintenance itself involves modifying existing software to correct faults, improve performance, or adapt to new conditions, with a goal of extending its useful life. While the course structure includes coursework and an exam, it also delves into concepts like DevOps, a methodology emphasizing collaboration and automation between development and operations teams, which aims to improve the efficiency and appeal of software maintenance by fostering a \"you build it, you own it\" philosophy and integrating maintenance into the overall DevOps lifecycle.', '2025-11-14 14:21:36'),
(101, 2000000044, 'AWS Disaster Recovery Strategies', 'This module prepares individuals to design disaster recovery strategies by identifying approaches like defining Recovery Point Objectives (RPO) and Recovery Time Objectives (RTO) based on business needs, understanding AWS service categories for disaster planning, describing common DR patterns, and applying AWS Well-Architected Framework principles. It covers disaster planning strategies, AWS-specific DR solutions, various DR patterns such as backup and restore, pilot light, warm standby, and multi-site, and includes a guided lab on configuring hybrid storage with AWS Storage Gateway. Ultimately, the module equips aspiring cloud architects with the knowledge to mitigate disaster risks and ensure timely recovery, minimizing business impact.', '2025-11-19 07:18:14'),
(102, 2000000043, 'Software Maintenance and Evolution', 'This course, BMSE3014 Software Maintenance, covers the essential concepts of software maintenance and evolution, crucial for ensuring software relevance and longevity. The course structure includes a 60% coursework component (group assignment and test) and a 40% exam, focusing on how software systems adapt to changing user demands and environments. Key topics include software evolution, the importance of sustainment, and basic maintenance concepts, emphasizing the systematic modification of software to correct faults, improve performance, and adapt to new conditions. Furthermore, the course delves into DevOps, a methodology that integrates development and operations to streamline application delivery through automation and collaboration, and explores its impact on making software maintenance a more integral and appealing part of the software lifecycle.', '2025-11-19 07:32:42'),
(103, 2000000043, 'Software Maintenance and DevOps', 'This course on Software Maintenance (BMSE3014) covers essential concepts from software evolution and sustainment to the fundamental practices of maintenance. Software evolution is the ongoing enhancement of software to meet changing needs and improve relevance, while software sustainment involves the processes, people, and resources to support operational software. The course will be assessed through coursework (60%), including a group assignment and a test, and a final exam (40%). It also explores the DevOps methodology, which integrates development and operations to streamline software delivery through continuous integration, delivery, and automated processes, ultimately impacting how software maintenance is approached and integrated.', '2025-11-19 07:35:54');

